body:
 I wrote a wrapper for Hashset, and tried to compare two set with same elements. But compiler complained `== cannot be applied to type HashSet` even if I derived PartialEq(Hashset implement PartialEq and Eq traits).

Compiler suggest `add #[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq + std::cmp::PartialEq)]`. 
I asked question at [forum](https://users.rust-lang.org/t/cannot-be-applied-to-type-hashset/59313), and some people said it looks like a bug.
[playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&edition=2018&gist=ccead07f40191c3dfde5b541d2a3b1e6)

```rust
use std::collections::HashSet;
use std::hash::Hash;

#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq)]
pub struct CustomSet<T> {
    set: HashSet<T>,
}

impl<T> CustomSet<T>
where
    T: Eq + PartialEq + Hash + Copy,
{
    pub fn new(_input: &[T]) -> Self {
        let mut set: HashSet<T> = HashSet::new();
        for &i in _input {
            set.insert(i);
        }
        CustomSet { set }
    }
}

fn main() {
    let set1 = CustomSet::new(&[1, 2, 3]);
    let set2 = CustomSet::new(&[1, 2, 3]);
    assert_eq!(set1, set2);
}

```
